task.summary: attempted a ui change with the original input buttons. hopefully everything checks out, but we should definitely double-check if it correctly gets file contents after this commit.
fixed the selectFile and Submit buttons along with the display on textbox.
changed recursion to a while loop in algorithm
added margin-bottom for better visual of output; set encoding of file reader to 'ASCII' as a test to see if it will take in google sheets' outputted TSV files.
added specifications for unclassifieds (along with the line, we now also know a probable reason).

test 1: attempt at removing CRLF line terminators which are part of the .tsv files generated from Google Sheets. I've learned that once you can remove those CRLF line terminators, then EasyRide will be able to properly read/parse the .tsv. CRLF Line terminators are from window's text files and I believe they're symbolized through /r/n while on Unix systems, \n is used. This is my first attempt at our biggest bug.
tidying up console output, edited some alignment on website, and tweaked some code. update: my test did work and now EasyRide can process .tsv files generated from google sheets!
